If you&#39;re going to test lots of servlets, consider writing fake 
HttpServletRequest and HttpServletResponse. 
The response could f.i. provide a fake Printwriter that records 
what&#39;s printed on him. 
Test the doGet() method as any other method. Make a new HelloWorld()
and call its doGet() with your fake request and response. After 
execution you can inspect the changes in request and response. In 
your case : get the fake writer and check the printed lines.
Your tests will run without the server running. You&#39;re only testing 
the class and not f.i. the configuration of the server.

The fake requests and responses can be found on the internet, 
google &quot;MockHttpServletRequest&quot;.
I took the sourcecode from http://mockrunner.sourceforge.net/ and 
modified(simplified) the code for my use.

Hope it helps,

Bart

&gt; public class HelloWorld extends HttpServlet {
&gt;     public void doGet(HttpServletRequest request, 
&gt; HttpServletResponse response)
&gt;     throws IOException, ServletException
&gt;     {
&gt;         response.setContentType(&quot;text/html&quot;);
&gt;         PrintWriter out = response.getWriter();
&gt;         out.println(&quot;&lt;html&gt;&quot;);
&gt;         out.println(&quot;&lt;head&gt;&quot;);
&gt;         //out.println(&quot;&lt;title&gt;Hello World!&lt;/title&gt;&quot;);
&gt;         out.println(&quot;&lt;/head&gt;&quot;);
&gt;         out.println(&quot;&lt;body&gt;&quot;);
&gt;         out.println(&quot;&lt;h1&gt;Hello World!&lt;/h1&gt;&quot;);
&gt;         out.println(&quot;&lt;/body&gt;&quot;);
&gt;         out.println(&quot;&lt;/html&gt;&quot;);
&gt;     }
&gt;     public void doPost(HttpServletRequest request, 
&gt; HttpServletResponse response)
&gt;     throws IOException, ServletException {
&gt;         doGet(request, response);
&gt;     }
&gt; }
&gt; 
&gt; *********************TEST CASE BEGIN*********************
&gt; public class HelloWorldTest extends ServletTestCase{ 
&gt; 
&gt;     public void testDoGet() {
&gt;        HelloWorld hw = new HelloWorld();
&gt;        try {
&gt;            hw.doGet(request,response); 
&gt;        }catch (Exception e) { }
&gt;     }
&gt;     
&gt;     public void endDoGet(WebResponse theResponse) {
&gt;         String expected = &quot;&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body&gt;&lt;h1&gt;Hello World!
&gt; &lt;/h1&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;&quot;;
&gt;         String actual = theResponse.getText();
&gt;         
&gt;         assertEquals(expected,actual);
&gt;     }
&gt; }
